{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## S8 done — 2026-06-30. docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md + README link.\n\n- AC1: docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md is a complete ordered client walkthrough — 12 sections covering all 8 steps (provision AWS -> deploy Gerrit+review-bot -> project/label/submit-req -> bot/webhooks/events-log -> review->vote pipe (+/rerun) -> replication -> GitHub lock -> verify/operate), each referencing the committed infra/ artifacts + ADRs 0007-0014.\n- AC2: NO secrets. Scan over all committed docs/infra/src found only rebar's OWN secret-scanner test fixtures (AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE = AWS public doc example; an RSA-marker test string) in tests/unit/workflow/test_lint.py — fake values, not real, not in the doc/infra. The literal account id 896586841071 does NOT appear in the client doc (placeholder <aws-account-id>). .env / SSH keys / voted.db are gitignored (not tracked).\n- AC3: linked from README (Install section, an OPTIONAL/ADVANCED blockquote) — discoverable but explicitly not required for standard rebar use.\n- AC4: the secret-handling section (placed first) documents the /rebar/prod/* SSM SecureString -> ephemeral 0600 .env model (ADR-0008/0012) and that no credential is ever committed.\n\nReview: docs-only ticket — self-verified AC coverage + the no-secrets scan (rather than an adversarial code-review subagent, which applies to code stories)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782815149249521001,"uuid":"b95dc9c1-466b-443c-8f85-c22fdd89c096"}